# Fix Gradient Button Light Mode

## Overview
ConfirmDialog delete button was invisible in light mode due to missing gradient background CSS.

## Problem
- `bg-gradient-button-danger` class not being generated by Tailwind
- Tailwind's `backgroundImage` extensions don't work reliably with hyphenated names
- Result: white text on white/transparent background in light mode

## Solution
Added explicit CSS utility classes in `@layer utilities` section of index.css:
- `.bg-gradient-button-primary`
- `.bg-gradient-button-danger`
- `.bg-gradient-button-success`

Also added to Tailwind safelist for consistency.

## Files Modified
- [x] `src/index.css` - Added gradient button CSS utilities
- [x] `tailwind.config.js` - Added gradient classes to safelist

## Testing
- [x] Type check passes
- [x] Build successful
- [x] Gradient classes verified in built CSS output

## Review
Fixed in one commit. Root cause: Tailwind's backgroundImage theme extension wasn't generating the classes despite being in the config. Moving definitions to explicit CSS utilities in `@layer utilities` ensures they're always generated.
